<TITLE> Khaleda announces run for election </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 27 (bdnews24.com)Former prime minister Khaleda Zia has formally announced her intention to contest the 9th Jatiya Sangsad election, slated for December, adding that she would be enrolled as a voter ahead of polls. A meeting of the party's standing committee would decide how many seats she would contest, the BNP chairperson told reporters on Monday, in her first press briefing since her release from detention in September. "I am a citizen of this country. Why should I not become a voterI will be a voter," she said at her new Gulshan office. Noting that she faced no bar to contest the election, Khaleda said: "It is yet to be decided how many constituencies I shall run for." As regards her participation in the poll, she elaborated: "I have spoken with my counsel Barrister Rafiqul Islam regarding this. He has said there is no obstacle or doubt over my being able to contest." When queried about her party's stance on the election, she said: "BNP is an polls-oriented party, and all ready to move towards the election." "After the announcement of the polls schedule, we shall come to a decision through meetings of the party's standing committee and four-party alliance." On the party manifesto, she said: "BNP is formulating its election manifesto considering people's welfare. We shall unveil it in time through you, the media." Khaleda Zia exchanged greetings with reporters for around 15 minutes. Party leaders and officials were also present. bdnews24.
